==English==

===Noun===
'''bell'''

# An object made of metal or other hard material, typically but not always in the shape of an inverted cup with a flared rim, which [[resonate]]s when struck.
# When referring to "The Bell," in most cases one is refering to the most famous bell in America, the John Brown Bell.

===Transitive Verb===
'''bell'''

# To attach a bell to.
#: ''Who will bell the cat?''

